Caltex Petroleum Corp, a joint venturebetween Chevron Corp &lt;CHV> and Texaco Inc &lt;TX>, said it raisedposted prices for several petroleum products in Singapore,effective today.     The company said its naphtha posting is up three cts agallon to 43 cts. It said it is raising jet and kerosenepostings 2.5 cts, bringing jet to 52.5 cts and kerosene to 51.5cts.    Diesel grades are up two cts, Caltex said, bringing bothdiesel gas oil (one pct sulfur) and 52-57 D.I. (55 cetane) to52 cts a gallon, and diesel gas oil (0.5 pct) to 52 cts.    The company said it is increasing medium and heavy fuel oilpostings by one dlr a barrel. Medium is now 15.50 dlrs abarrel, and heavy fuel is 14.75 dlrs. Reuter&#3;